{"title": "As political parties court votes, India debates if caste census will secure jobs or divide country", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2023-10-20", "content": "BENGALURU/NEW DELHI - Mr Babban Sahani was just 15 when he had to drop out of school to support his family. A member of the Mallah fishing community \u2013 classified as an \u201cextremely backward caste\u201d \u2013 in eastern Indian state Bihar, he was sent to neighbouring Nepal to learn to paint houses.\n\u201cWe didn\u2019t even have enough to eat back then,\u201d the 40-year-old said."}